kelmore5.java.yeh.data_structures.linked_lists

Class DoubleCircularLinkedList<T>

  • java.lang.Object
    • kelmore5.java.yeh.data_structures.linked_lists.ListAdapter<T>
      • kelmore5.java.yeh.data_structures.linked_lists.DoubleCircularLinkedList<T>
  • Type Parameters:
    T - the type parameter
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Iterable<T>, java.util.Collection<T>, java.util.List<T>

    class DoubleCircularLinkedList<T>
extends ListAdapter<T>
     A Double Circular Linked List is similar to a CircularLinkedList. Where a Circular Linked List
 allows the user to travel continuously through the linked list (looping from the back to the front of
 the list), a double circular linked list has the additional ability to travel backward as well as forward.
    Date:
    Fall 2012
